*Bringing Precision Pricing to Every Participant*


Until now, participant pricing could only follow what was set at the
network level, limiting flexibility when exceptions were needed.

With this update, network owners and managers can now enable *Custom Rule*
on the participant=E2=80=99s network, allowing you to override network pric=
ing and
define participant-specific *External* and *Internal* prices when required.
Why We Built This

Some participants require special rates, unique surge rules, or different
payout structures =E2=80=94 but changing the entire network to accommodate =
one
participant was never ideal.

The *Custom Rule* toggle introduces a controlled way to create these
exceptions without breaking the network=E2=80=99s pricing model.
What=E2=80=99s New


Custom Rule Toggle at the Participant Level

Each participant now has a *Custom Rule* switch.

   -

   *Off (Default)*

   The participant uses all *network-level pricing*.


   -

   *On*

   The network owner can define *participant-specific pricing*, overriding
   what was set at the network level.



This allows you to set custom service rates, surges, rain charges, waiting
charges, and any other pricing logic.

Participant-Type Aware Pricing

The pricing view automatically adapts based on the type of participant:

   -

   *Supply Participants* will only see *Internal Price*, since this
   represents the service rates negotiated with suppliers.
   -

   *Demand Participants* will only see *External Price*, since this
   represents the service rates negotiated with the demand side.



This ensures every participant sees only the pricing that is relevant to
their role in the network, keeping configurations focused, accurate, and
clutter-free.
What This Means For You

At the participant level, you can now decide exactly where network pricing
applies and where it doesn=E2=80=99t.

This means:

   -

   Network-wide pricing remains your default
   -

   Exceptions can be created only when needed
   -

   Participant-specific economics stay isolated and safe


Your network stays consistent, while flexibility exists where it truly
matters.
